(7, 1, '2013-04-29 01:08:32', '2013-04-29 01:08:32', '<h1>Vent Cleaning - Hidden Values</h1>\r\nVent cleaning is often an under appreciated area of maintenance in your heating and cooling systems. By maintaining proper clean vents, you can minimize air born allergens and improve energy efficiencies associated with your HVAC systems.\r\n\r\nLearn more from our <a href="http://www.1responsehvac.com/vent-cleaning-facts.html">vent cleaning facts page</a>.\r\n\r\nLearn more about the values of vent cleaning at <a title="NADCA vent cleaning facts" href="http://www.nadca.com/consumerinformation/residentialconsumer.aspx" target="_blank">NADCA faq page</a>.\r\n<h3>NADCA Member</h3>\r\n<img title="NADCA vent cleaning" alt="NADCA - vent cleaning" src="http://www.1responsehvac.com/images/duct_cleaning/nadcalogo_banner.gif" width="134" height="114" align="right" border="0" hspace="0" vspace="0" />The National Air Duct Cleaners Association (NADCA) was formed in 1989 as a non-profit association of companies engaged in the cleaning of HVAC systems. Its mission was to promote source removal as the only acceptable method of cleaning and to establish industry standards for the association.\r\n<h3>Benefits of Using NADCA Member</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>NADCA members abide by a code of ethics that promises members will "serve our customers with integrity and competence". Learn more about the <a href="http://www.nadca.com/consumerinformation/codeofethics.aspx">code of ethics</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>All members are required to perform work in accordance with NADCA Standards. As part of its Quality Assurance Program, NADCA provides information about how to select a qualified contractor along with pre - and post-cleaning checklists to ensure that total system cleaning is performed</li>\r\n</ol>', 'Vent Cleaning', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'next-page', '', '', '2013-05-04 15:53:07', '2013-05-04 15:53:07', '', 0, 'http://1responsehvac.com/?page_id=7', 0, 'page', '', 0),
