(88, 1, '2013-05-04 16:53:04', '2013-05-04 16:53:04', '<h1> Lint Fires Are Real</h1>\r\n<img class="alignright" alt="" src="http://www.1responsehvac.com/images/lint_fire/house-fire.jpg" width="320" height="240" align="left" />\r\n\r\nLint fires are a terrifying reality that can be easily avoided, which is why <i>First Response Air Conditioning &amp; Heating Purification</i> proudly supports Lint Alert. By spending a just a few extra dollars, a home owner can protect their family and home from the dangers associated with using a clothes dryer. Clothes dryers are not inherently dangerous; however when proper maintenance and precautions are not taken, it is very possible to subject yourself to unnecessary risk.\r\n\r\nSpending just a few dollars to protect you and your family from the dangers of improper maintenance of your dryer can save lives. Please ask about the services and products we offer to help protect you and your family.\r\n\r\n<b><i>Summary of United State Fire Administration:</i></b>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Clothes dryer fires account for about 15,600 structure fires, 15 deaths, and 400 injuries annually.</li>\r\n	<li>Eighty percent of clothes dryer fires in structures occur in residential buildings.</li>\r\n	<li>Annually, 12,700 clothes dryer fires occur in residential buildings resulting in 15 deaths and 300 injuries.</li>\r\n	<li>"Failure to clean" is the leading factor contributing to clothes dryer fires in residential buildings.</li>\r\n	<li>New home construction trends place clothes dryers and washing machines in more hazardous locations away from outside walls such as bedrooms, second-floor hallways, bathrooms, and kitchens.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Learn More Watching This Video</h2>\r\n<div id="mediaspace" style="margin: 10px;">Video Loading...</div>\r\n<script type="text/javascript" src="/mediaplayer/swfobject.js"></script><script type="text/javascript">// <![CDATA[\r\nvar so = new SWFObject(''/mediaplayer/player.swf'',''ply'',''470'',''320'',''9'',''#00000